                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/619: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-07T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 7, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 7—8:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your circular telegram dated December 5, 4 p.m.<note n="88" xml:id="d357fn88"
                        >Not printed.</note> Danish Government expresses sympathy with initiative
                    taken by principal powers with respect to Pact of Paris, but considers it must
                    postpone definite decision as to participation in view of developments since
                    date of Department’s circular of December 1, 4 p.m. Foreign Minister informs me
                    this decision in accord with attitude of other Scandinavian countries. Danish
                    press in general questions efficacy of the pact.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
